HEADWORD: Avicula
<hw>A*vic"u*la</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., small
bird.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of marine bivalves, having
a pearly interior, allied to the pearl oyster; -- so called from a
supposed resemblance of the typical species to a bird.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

